main event: A witness reported seeing a bright white, round object moving back and forth in the sky for 29 minutes on November 13, 1965.
interesting points: The object appeared to be the size of a saucer and was very bright.
The object was observed to move straight and gradually disappear.
The witness was on a hunting trip and happened to glance up and see the object at an elevation of 529-539 feet.
This was the second sighting in the same general area on consecutive nights, but there was no military or commercial air traffic reported on this occasion.
The reliability of the report was assessed as F-G (fair to good).
